{
  "texts": [
    "Note that M can also be set a priori from the macro-model or from ancillary imaging data as explained in Sect. 3.2.1.",
    "To first order, this method also generally works when the second lensed image is also microlensed (see appendix C of Sluse et al. 2012).",
    "In that case, only the relative microlensing between the pair of images is retrieved.",
    "When more than two lensed images are observed, the comparison between multiple pairs of images generally enables one to identify which image is minimally microlensed.",
    "There is a number of situations where the above decomposition does not work."
  ]
}